{
  "text": "Oxygen isotope compositions of mineral separates were measured at the CNR^IGG of Pisa, using the laser fluorination technique of [CITATION_1] . Mineral separates were obtained from crushed, sieved (0Á3 and 0Á5 mm fraction), and ultrasonically cleaned samples. Pure mineral fractions (499 vol. %) of quartz, kyanite, topaz and rutile were obtained by means of standard heavy liquid techniques, followed by hand-picking under a binocular microscope.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "97532496"
